text:
<@U11HH3P7Y>: Any idea why `make unit-test` runs in `before_script` instead of `script`? <https://github.com/hyperledger/fabric/blob/master/.travis.yml#L41>

I’m looking to run `make linter` first and wasn’t sure if I should put that in `before_script`
if we keep `make unit-test` in script section -  Travis execute behave test cases even though there is a failure in unit-tests.
I see
so I’m going to change it to
<@U0TFEHX8E|sheehan> uploaded a file: <https://hyperledgerproject.slack.com/files/sheehan/F1HKKLG2J/pasted_image_at_2016_06_16_02_40_pm.png|Pasted image at 2016-06-16, 2:40 PM>
idea is to fail fast if there’s a linter problem so the dev can resolve it without waiting for the other tests
It doesn’t have the same problem as `unit-test` where sometimes there are flapping tests
yes you can change that but if any failures in linter, travis won't execute unit-test tests
